snippet.textDisplay: For the first girl, I actually preffered her 1st result, "orange-blond". It shined more than the dull blond at the end, and it was full of more body, really enhanced her facial features more without needing heavy makeup. BUT I found I only liked it when her hair was in the front, and not raked back. It looked more poshy anime style, was really nice. The final end result was just... I didn't find it flattering to her skin tone at all, and just looked bleh even with her makeup on. Of course, I wasn't there, seeing it in all different kinds of light, and I'm not the one who has to wear it, taste differs from person to person.
